      "message": "wallet: Deserialize directly in CWalletTx's ctor\n\nWhen loading a transaction, instead of constructing a CWalletTx with no\ntransaction, pass the DataStream into the constructor so that the\nCWalletTx is RAII. This allows us to ensure that the transaction is\nnever a nullptr so that dereferences, especially once multiple txs are\nstored, will not cause a segfault.",
      "committer": {
        "name": "Ava Chow",
        "email": "github@achow101.com",
        "date": "2026-06-09T22:54:49Z"
      },
